    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-22T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="150"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60i31/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Estonia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Carlson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tallinn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-22T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 22, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 22—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Referring to Legation’s telegram No. 3 of February 27,<note n="21"
                        xml:id="d150fn21">Not printed.</note> the Ministry for Foreign Affairs has
                    just handed me a note, dated May 21,<note n="21" xml:id="d150fn22">Not
                        printed.</note> which after reciting the provisions of article No. 29 of the
                    Treaty of Friendship Commerce and Consular Rights between the United States and
                    Estonia under which this treaty may be modified or terminated on May 22, 1936,
                    proceeds as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“With reference to this stipulation the Ministry for Foreign Affairs has
                            the honor to ask the American Legation to kindly convey to the notice of
                            its government that the Estonian Government would like to see this
                            treaty modified from the said date of May 22, 1936, onwards.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In the note the wish is expressed for the holding of the treaty revision
                    negotiations at Tallinn and for the setting of the date for the opening of the
                    negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carlson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
